#: ../../H/heavyweight.rst:5
msgid "heavyweight"
msgstr "heavyweight"

#: ../../H/heavyweight.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../H/heavyweight.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] High-overhead; :ref:`baroque`\\; code-intensive; featureful, but "
"costly. Esp. used of communication protocols, language designs, and any sort"
" of implementation in which maximum generality and/or ease of implementation"
" has been pushed at the expense of mundane considerations such as speed, "
"memory utilization, and startup time. :ref:`EMACS` is a heavyweight editor; "
":ref:`X` is an *extremely* heavyweight window system. This term isn't "
"pejorative, but one hacker's heavyweight is another's :ref:`elephantine` and"
" a third's :ref:`monstrosity`\\. Oppose lightweight. Usage: now borders on "
"techspeak, especially in the compound heavyweight process."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]オーバーヘッドが高い、\\ :ref:`baroque`\\ "
"、コードを大量に使う、機能豊富だがコストが高い。特に、通信プロトコル、言語設計、そして最大の一般性かつ/または実装の容易さが、速度、メモリ利用、起動時間といった平凡な考慮事項を犠牲にして推し進められたあらゆる種類の実装について使われる。\\"
" :ref:`EMACS`\\ はheavyweightなエディタである。\\ :ref:`X`\\ は\\ *極めて*\\ "
"heavyweightなウィンドウシステムである。この用語は軽蔑的ではないが、あるハッカーのheavyweightは別のハッカーの\\ "
":ref:`elephantine`\\ であり、三人目の\\ :ref:`monstrosity`\\ "
"である。lightweightと対立する。用法:今やtechspeakの域に近づいており、特に複合語heavyweight processで。"
